<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM VETERANS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  1  4:43:18 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I'm an Australian Vietnam Vet 68/69. I just had to write and congradulate you on a great site. Us Aussies had the same troubles coming home as you blokes. Two failed marriages and twenty years or so of pain, I'm still struggling with Vietnam. I am handling it OK now, but there were times!!!!.<br>
I'm trying to put a site up with from the Aussie view-point. You can find it at http://users.mildura.net.au/users/marshall<br>
Sites like yours are important. The mistakes made by governments, should not be passed on to the soldiers who only did there duty. We owe it to those who can't speak to tell the truth. Now might be the right time to start rewriting history and do just that -tell the truth.
<p><code>-- marshall@mildura.net.au  (Ern Marshall) </code><p>


